[src:longest-common-subsequence/dynamic-programming] There are two key attributes that a problem must have in order for dynamic programming to be applicable: optimal substructure and overlapping sub-problems.
[src:longest-common-subsequence/dynamic-programming] If a problem can be solved by combining optimal solutions to *non-overlapping* sub-problems, the strategy is called "divide and conquer" instead.
