[src:longest-common-subsequence/longest-common-subsequence] The longest common subsequence between X and Y is "`MJAU`".
[src:longest-common-subsequence/longest-common-subsequence] The table `C` shown below, which is generated by the function `LCSLength`, shows the lengths of the longest common subsequences between prefixes of X and Y .
[src:longest-common-subsequence/longest-common-subsequence] The i th row and j th column shows the length of the LCS between $X_{1..i}$ and $Y_{1..j}$ .
